All you what need:
* An Amiga or compatible computer
* OS 3.0+
* a 68020 CPU or faster
* a Harddisc with +200 kb space
* Gui4Cli 3.8.5 (Interpreter is included)
* a fast mouse, 400 dpi or better 560 dpi


The Plot:
You are a pilot of a X-Wing "X-2200", you flying through an enemy sector.
Your "Type II" Quad-Laser are a good weapon for Space-Fights.


Your Mission:
Destroy so much enemy Space-Ships you can,
and earn so much points, is possible!!!

The maximum of point is 99999.

The bar on bottom shows your power (max. 100%). Every played second you loose 1%
of power and earn one point - nice or?!

The game is over, if your power is zero or you reaching 99999 points.


The Controls:
Just shot (clicking) with your mouse on the objects, they appear.

 Hit fellowing keys
	on title:    CTRL+Q = Quitting Game
	during play: Q      = Leave/Abort Game
					 P      = Game Paused
					 C      = Will change Cockpit-View
	after game:  Space  = Go back to Title


Fellowing objects exists in game:
	o Asteriod = There are much of them in this sector
					 Has no Weapons, just destroy it for some points.
					 Points: 150

	o Mine = A Pulsar-Mine "PM 3X12" is extremly dangerous.
				His Weapon is a very explosive pulsar detonator, and hyperwaves
				sensors for locating an enemy space-ship
				(you are one of this enemy space-ship)
				Don't touch it, destroy it so fast as you can or you're dead!
				Points: 200

	o U.F.O. = Type & Weapons unknown - Just destroy it!!!
				  Points: 250

	o Fighter = "FX-120 C" Combat-Fighter is very small (and fast)
					His "Type I" Lasers is a poor weapon.
					Points: 300

	o Battlestar = A very dangerous Space-Ship his fire-power is giantic.
						The Battlestar "BST 3000" is small but deadly with his
						Photon-Torpetoes (like them in ST).
						Points: 350

	o X-Wing = "X-TR 100-V" is the newest X-Wing, taller but slower like yours.
				  His "Type III" Lasers are very effective, and powerfuller
				  like your "Type II" Lasers, and the Lase will overheating faster.
				  Points: 400

	o Jet = The "F-120 S" is a very old jetplane, he was one of the first Space-Ships.
			  The jet holds four plasma-rockets under his wings - so be careful!
			  Points: 450

	o Sometimes crossing Bonus-Capsules your way:
		 10% of power and 100 points more
		 10% of power and 100 points less
		 500 points will increased your score
		 500 points will decreased your score
	  A Surprise-Capsules (a capsule with a "?" on it)
	  can hold one of a Bonus above (Be warned - You never know what's in it)


After played game you became some Bonus-Points for every played seconds and
destroyed enemy Space-Ship.



